Serialized Form

  • Package com.shouldis.bitset

    • Class com.shouldis.bitset.BitSet extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • size
          int size
          The number of indices accessible by this BitSet. Indices 0 through size -1 are accessible.
        • wordCount
          int wordCount
          The number of long words contained by this BitSet. Equal to ceiling(BitSet.size / 64) and BitSet.words.length.
        • words
          long[] words
          Array holding the long words whose bits are manipulated. Has length ceiling(BitSet.size / 64). Though this has protected visibility, using methods such as BitSet.getWord(int), BitSet.setWord(int, long), BitSet.andWord(int, long) is preferred over direct access.

  • Package com.shouldis.bitset.random

    • Class com.shouldis.bitset.random.DensityRandom extends Random implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • bitsConsumed
          int bitsConsumed
          The internal counter to track how many bits of DensityRandom.booleanWord have been consumed by DensityRandom.nextBoolean().
        • booleanWord
          long booleanWord
          The field of bits used by DensityRandom.nextBoolean() to more efficiently produce boolean values which are true at the rate determined by DensityRandom.density. This field is refreshed with DensityRandom.nextLong() after all bits have been consumed.
        • density
          double density
          The density of words generated by DensityRandom.nextInt(), DensityRandom.nextLong(), and the rate at which DensityRandom.nextBoolean() returns true. Integers will have on average (DensityRandom.density * 32) bits in the live state, and longs will have (DensityRandom.density * 64) bits in the live state, with each generated bit having a chance equal to DensityRandom.density to be in the live state.
        • depth
          int depth
          The depth, or number of operations performed in order to achieve an estimation of DensityRandom.density. This value is bounded to the range [1, 63] by DensityRandom.boundDepth(int), resulting in an accuracy of up to 2-64.
        • sequence
          long sequence
          The sequence of operations used to operate uniformly distributed random bits against each-other in order to generate specified density.

      • Serialized Fields

        • state

          Internal value used to store the current value held by this generator.
